Monte nuovo presents a crater [Small ink sketch] internally carved
with mud the brim of the mountain is formed of pumice & volcanic
ashes. a quantity of lava has burst out on the south side;
but this seems to have been rather an immense
mass projected than a stream forming a stratum
- throughout the whole campania of Rome, much
ashes, then lava then ashes, [underline]lava then [deletion]a[/deletion] tufa[/underline]. the
tufa often the last stratum. Then [insertion]on[/insertion] this day to
examine the tufa of [underline]Herculaneum[/underline].-

